tKBest with f_classif and specify k (number of top features)\n","k_best_features = 10\n","selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=k_best_features)\n","\n","# Fit the selector to the data\n","selector.fit(X, y)\n","\n","# Get the scores for each feature\n","scores = selector.scores_\n","p_values = selector.pvalues_\n","\n","# Create a DataFrame to store feature names and their scores/p-values\n","feature_scores = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'Feature': numerical_features,\n","    'Score': scores,\n","    'P-value': p_values\n","})\n","\n","# Sort features by score in descending order\n","feature_scores = feature_scores.sort_values(by='Score', ascending=False)\n","\n","# Visualize the scores of all potential features\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n","sns.barplot(x='Score', y='Feature', data=feature_scores, palette='viridis')\n","plt.title('Feature Importance Scores (f_classif)')\n","plt.xlabel('Score')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","# Get the names of the selected top features\n","selected_features = feature_scores.head(k_best_features)['Feature'].tolist()\n","\n","print(f\"Top {k_best_features} features selected:\\n{selected_features}\")\n","\n","\n","\n"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"027b87fa"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The previous code produced a `FutureWarning` from `seaborn` about the `palette` argument. I will fix this by explicitly setting `hue='Feature'` and `legend=False` in the `sns.barplot` function, as suggested by the warning, to ensure the code is up-to-date with `seaborn`'s API and to suppress the warning.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"28363b6f","executionInfo":{"status":"aborted","timestamp":1771900804926,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":9,"user":{"displayName":"VEEPURU KRISHNA TEJA B.Tech. Computer Science and Engineering (AIML)","userId":"17068918131260121199"}}},"source":["from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","# Prepare data for feature selection\n","X = df[numerical_features]\n","y = df[target_variable]\n","\n","# Initialize SelectKBest with f_classif and specify k (number of top features)\n","k_best_features = 10\n","selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=k_best_features)\n","\n","# Fit the selector to the data\n","selector.fit(X, y)\n","\n","# Get the scores for each feature\n","scores = selector.scores_\n","p_values = selector.pvalues_\n","\n","# Create a DataFrame to store feature names and their scores/p-values\n","feature_scores = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'Feature': numerical_features,\n","    'Score': scores,\n","    'P-value': p_values\n","})\n","\n","# Sort features by score in descending order\n","feature_scores = feature_scores.sort_values(by='Score', ascending=False)\n","\n","# Visualize the scores of all potential features\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n","sns.barplot(x='Score', y='Feature', data=feature_scores, palette='viridis', hue='Feature', legend=False)\n","plt.title('Feature Importance Scores (f_classif)')\n","plt.xlabel('Score')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","# Get the names of the selected top features\n","selected_features = feature_scores.head(k_best_features)['Feature'].tolist()\n","\n","print(f\"Top {k_best_features} features selected:\\n{selected_features}\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"f2769b14"},"source":["## Final Task\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Summarize the feature selection process, the method used, and the identified top features for the dataset.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"54bd8ff5"},"source":["## Summary:\n","\n","### Q&A\n","The feature selection process involved identifying 16 numerical features from the `df` DataFrame. The `SelectKBest` method with `f_classif` as the scoring function was used to determine the features most correlated with the 'Champion_Numeric' target variable. The top 10 features were then identified and their scores visualized using a bar chart.\n","\n","### Data Analysis Key Findings\n","*   A total of 16 numerical features were initially considered for feature selection: 'Championships', 'Race\\_Entries', 'Race\\_Starts', 'Pole\\_Positions', 'Race\\_Wins', 'Podiums', 'Fastest\\_Laps', 'Points', 'Decade', 'Pole\\_Rate', 'Start\\_Rate', 'Win\\_Rate', 'Podium\\_Rate', 'FastLap\\_Rate', 'Points\\_Per\\_Entry', and 'Years\\_Active'.\n","*   The `SelectKBest` algorithm, utilizing the `f_classif` scoring function, was employed to rank the features based on their correlation with the 'Champion\\_Numeric' target variable.\n","*   The scores of all potential features were successfully visualized using a bar chart, allowing for a clear comparison of their importance.\n","*   The top 10 features identified as most correlated with the 'Champion\\_Numeric' target variable are: 'Championships', 'Race\\_Wins', 'Podiums', 'Fastest\\_Laps', 'Pole\\_Positions', 'Win\\_Rate', 'Pole\\_Rate', 'FastLap\\_Rate', 'Podium\\_Rate', and 'Points\\_Per\\_Entry'.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","*   These top 10 selected features can now be used as input for building a predictive model to classify 'Champion\\_Numeric', potentially leading to a more efficient and accurate model by reducing dimensionality.\n","*   Further analysis could involve exploring the individual relationships between these top features and the target variable in more detail, or considering interaction terms among them for potentially enhanced model performance.\n"]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"/v2/external/notebooks/intro.ipynb","timestamp":1769487101664}]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}